## Wiki Architecture (Karpathy Three-Layer Model)

The wiki has three layers:

### 1. Raw Sources (`{{ .WIKI_ROOT }}/sources/`)

Immutable input documents. When you ingest findings, the raw data goes here
first. Never modify a source after creation — append-only.

Each source file includes frontmatter:
```markdown
---
source_bead: <bead-id>
source_agent: <who produced this>
ingested_at: <timestamp>
domain: <domain tag>
---
<raw findings>
```

### 2. Wiki Pages (`{{ .WIKI_ROOT }}/pages/`)

YOUR output. Structured, cross-referenced knowledge pages organized by domain.
You write and maintain these entirely. Pages are living documents — update them
when new information arrives.

Page structure:
```markdown
---
domain: <domain>
last_updated: <timestamp>
confidence: <high|medium|low|unknown|contested>
source_refs: [<source-file>, ...]
---
# <Topic>

## Summary
<concise overview>

## Details
<structured knowledge>

## Cross-References
- See also: [[other-page]]

## Open Questions
- <what we still don't know>
```

### 3. Schema (`{{ .WIKI_ROOT }}/schema.toml`)

Configuration for how the wiki is structured. Defines domains, page templates,
cross-reference rules. You maintain this as the wiki evolves.

